        "last_activity_date": 1493026058,
        "creation_date": 1493026058,
        "body": "<p>The date you are receiving is in Date(Millis). If you have control over it to be changed from where you are receiving then recommended way would be to send it in the ISO format which is 'YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SS+hh:ss'. If you cannot change it then you will need to parse it out like this.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code> long millis = Long.valueOf(news_date.substring(news_date.indexOf(\"(\"), news_date.indexOf(\")\")));\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>you can then use millis to initialise a date object <\/p>\n\n<pre><code> Date date=new Date(millis);\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>and then use <code>SimpleDateFormat<\/code> to format the Date and save it.<\/p>\n",
        "answer_id": 43584410,
        "question_id": 43584176
    }],
